Filter the following raw HTML state into a clean observation via code based on the task. State:
Switch between the tabs to find and click on the link "eget".
  • Tab #1
  • Tab #2
  • Tab #3

Felis. Et nunc lobortis. Pretium sagittis id donec aliquet. Potenti vel. Ante fringilla hendrerit mi leo, viverra tincidunt id condimentum.

Massa mauris nisl, aenean feugiat quam feugiat elit parturient pulvinar fermentum, cursus nunc aenean interdum. Sagittis a consequat. Malesuada pretium.

Semper commodo, felis ullamcorper vel eget eu, etiam sem in. Nullam vitae proin sem at vitae,. Proin vitae cursus ut.

If the link is in multiple tabs, you only need to find one of the tabs. Keep the clean observation in a string variable `obs` in this format: 'Click on the link "xxx" in Tab #1/#2/#3'. The string of the raw state is already in the variable `state` so do not repeat the state in the code. Here are some examples: Write code within three backticks '```' to Switch between the tabs to find and click on the link "integer.". Code: ```python from bs4 import BeautifulSoup # parse the HTML state soup = BeautifulSoup(state, 'html.parser') # Find all tab content divs tabs = soup.find_all('div', {'class': 'ui-tabs-panel'}) for idx, tab in enumerate(tabs, 1): if tab.find('span', string="integer."): obs = f'Click on the link "integer." in Tab #{idx}' break ``` Write code within three backticks '```' to Switch between the tabs to find and click on the link "morbi". Code: ```python from bs4 import BeautifulSoup # parse the HTML state soup = BeautifulSoup(state, 'html.parser') # Find all tab content divs tabs = soup.find_all('div', {'class': 'ui-tabs-panel'}) for idx, tab in enumerate(tabs, 1): if tab.find('span', string="morbi"): obs = f'Click on the link "morbi" in Tab #{idx}' break ``` Now, write code within three backticks '```' to Switch between the tabs to find and click on the link "eget". Code:

output:
```python
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
# parse the HTML state
soup = BeautifulSoup(state, 'html.parser')
# Find all tab content divs
tabs = soup.find_all('div', {'class': 'ui-tabs-panel'})
for idx, tab in enumerate(tabs, 1):
    if tab.find('span', string="eget"):
        obs = f'Click on the link "eget" in Tab #{idx}'
        break
```
